      "content": "interesting. so you're saying it was a humanitarian win but a strategic loss. but if you look at the actual outcome—the power vacuum, the rise of militias, and the whole region getting more unstable—doesn't that basically mean the intervention itself was a mistake from a realist perspective? like, if the end result is just more chaos, wasn't the whole thing objectively a failure?",
